libgrading
------------------------------------------
This is a simple library for grading C- and C++-language assignments. It runs
each test case in a child process in order to capture common programming
errors such as infinite loops and segmentation faults.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.6.1-1
  libdistance0-0.2.2-1bl2
  libgcc1-5.4.0-1
  libgrading-devel-0.1.2-1bl1
  libgrading0-0.1.2-1bl1
  libstdc++6-5.4.0-1
  pkg-config-0.29.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.25-4
  cmake-3.6.2-1
  cygport-0.23.0-1
  gcc-core-5.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-5.4.0-1
  make-4.2.1-1

Canonical website:
  http://trombonehero.github.io/libgrading/

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/trombonehero/libgrading/archive/v0.1.2.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libgrading-0.1.2-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libgrading-0.1.2-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libgrading-0.1.2-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libgrading-0.1.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libgrading0-0.1.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libgrading-devel-0.1.2-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libgrading)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libgrading.README
  /usr/share/doc/libgrading/README.md

(libgrading0)
  /usr/bin/cyggrading-0.dll

(libgrading-devel)
  /usr/include/libgrading.h
  /usr/lib/libgrading.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libgrading.pc

